---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/ui/PageHeader.astro';
import { getDb } from '../lib/context';
import { getProfile } from '../lib/repositories/about';
import { formatLongDate } from '../lib/utils/date';

const db = getDb();
const profile = await getProfile(db);

// The policy describes what this codebase actually does. If the data flows
// change, this page must change with them.
const lastUpdated = new Date('2026-07-11');
const contactEmail = profile?.email ?? 'oeyeci@gmail.com';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="What data this website collects, why, how long it is kept, and how to have it removed."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy policy"
    lead="This site collects as little as possible. Here is exactly what that means."
  />

  <div class="container-page pb-24">
    <div class="prose mx-auto max-w-[44rem]">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-subtle">
        Last updated: <time datetime={lastUpdated.toISOString()}>{formatLongDate(lastUpdated)}</time>
      </p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        This website sets no advertising cookies, runs no third-party trackers, and does not
        build a profile of you. The only personal data it stores is what you type into the
        contact form, and it is used solely to reply to you.
      </p>

      <h2>What is collected</h2>

      <h3>Contact form</h3>
      <p>
        When you send a message, the following is stored in a Cloudflare D1 database in order to
        read and reply to it:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name, email address, subject and message.</li>
        <li>
          Your IP address and browser user-agent, and the country Cloudflare associates with the
          request. These are kept only to identify and block spam.
        </li>
        <li>The time of submission.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The legal basis is legitimate interest: you contacted me and expect a reply. Messages are
        deleted once the correspondence is concluded, and in any case within 24 months.
      </p>

      <h3>Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        Traffic is measured with <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong>, which is
        privacy-first: it uses <strong>no cookies</strong>, does not fingerprint visitors, and
        does not track individuals across sites or sessions. It records aggregate page views,
        referrers and general performance timings. Nothing it collects identifies you.
      </p>

      <h3>Spam protection</h3>
      <p>
        The contact form is protected by <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong>, a CAPTCHA
        alternative that verifies you are human without tracking you and without the visual
        puzzles. It does not use cookies for cross-site tracking.
      </p>

      <h3>Security and delivery</h3>
      <p>
        The site runs on Cloudflare's network, which processes request metadata (IP address,
        user-agent, timestamps) in transient logs to deliver pages, mitigate attacks and detect
        abuse. This is standard for any website and is required for it to function at all.
      </p>

      <h2>What is stored in your browser</h2>
      <p>The site sets no tracking cookies. It stores exactly two things locally:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <code>theme</code> in <code>localStorage</code> — remembers whether you chose light or
          dark mode. It never leaves your device.
        </li>
        <li>
          A session cookie, <strong>only if you are the site administrator and sign in</strong>.
          It is <code>HttpOnly</code>, <code>Secure</code> and <code>SameSite=Lax</code>, and is
          used purely to keep that session authenticated.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Because no cookies are used for tracking or advertising, no cookie-consent banner is
        required.
      </p>

      <h2>What is shared</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing is sold, rented, or shared for marketing. Data is processed only by the services
        needed to run the site:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosting, database, media storage, analytics, spam protection.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Resend</strong> — used solely to email me a copy of your contact-form message so
          I see it promptly.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR and Turkey's KVKK you may request access to, correction of, or erasure of
        your personal data, and you may object to its processing. To exercise any of these, email{' '}
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> and I will respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        Pages here link to external sites (DOIs, publisher pages, ORCID, GitHub, Google Scholar).
        Those sites have their own privacy policies, and this one does not apply once you leave.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes, the "last updated" date above changes with it. Material changes
        will be noted on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy or data on this site can be sent to{' '}
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
